Remember me, don't you?

600
00:47:47,948 --> 00:47:49,617
I went and got you...

601
00:47:50,785 --> 00:47:52,495
...a candy bar.

602
00:47:52,787 --> 00:47:54,997
I thought you might be hungry.

603
00:47:56,248 --> 00:47:57,750
You hungry?

604
00:48:03,005 --> 00:48:05,341
You should try one of these.

605
00:48:20,648 --> 00:48:21,899
Hey there.

606
00:48:22,691 --> 00:48:26,362
Come here. Don't be afraid.
There's no reason to be afraid.

607
00:48:27,655 --> 00:48:28,989
Where'd you go?

608
00:48:30,324 --> 00:48:32,993
Where are you?
I know you're in there.

609
00:48:33,202 --> 00:48:35,037
I know you're under there.

610
00:48:36,580 --> 00:48:38,374
Come on, now.

611
00:48:38,833 --> 00:48:42,420
You're not still angry about
that little blood test, are you?

612
00:48:43,337 --> 00:48:45,881
Come on out.
Take a bite. Let me see you.

613
00:48:46,090 --> 00:48:48,717
I just wanna see you.

614
00:48:51,679 --> 00:48:54,849
You try some of this now.
I know you gotta be hungry.

615
00:48:56,392 --> 00:48:58,352
Yum, yum.

616
00:49:00,354 --> 00:49:03,065
There now. Don't you feel better?

617
00:49:26,046 --> 00:49:27,715
Mr. Hanson?

618
00:49:57,077 --> 00:49:59,788
Yum, yum.

619
00:51:43,267 --> 00:51:45,477
Gizmo ca-ca!

620
00:52:31,899 --> 00:52:33,817
Billy, are you okay?
Where are you?

621
00:52:34,234 --> 00:52:36,654
Mom, they hatched.
Get out of the house.

622
00:52:36,904 --> 00:52:39,239
Phone home. Ca-ca!

623
00:52:40,115 --> 00:52:42,409
Mom? Mom!

624
00:54:30,184 --> 00:54:32,227
Yum, yum.

625
00:55:09,181 --> 00:55:11,225
Get out of my kitchen!

626
00:57:06,089 --> 00:57:07,799
Neat!

627
00:57:27,694 --> 00:57:28,695
Hey!

628
00:57:34,284 --> 00:57:36,495
- Are you all right?
- I think so.

629
00:57:46,171 --> 00:57:47,756
Mom, it's Stripe!

630
00:57:59,226 --> 00:58:01,937
- Should I get it?
- Yeah, go ahead and get it.

631
00:58:02,354 --> 00:58:04,022
Oh, I didn't mean that.

632
00:58:05,023 --> 00:58:07,985
Hello, Dr. Molinaro.
Can we come in?

633
00:58:08,193 --> 00:58:10,278
My mom's had a bit of an accident.

634
00:58:12,447 --> 00:58:14,241
Be careful!

635
00:58:14,658 --> 00:58:15,909
What happened?

636
00:58:25,544 --> 00:58:26,795
Giz?

637
00:58:40,976 --> 00:58:42,853
Bright light! Bright light!

638
00:58:43,103 --> 00:58:44,479
Come here.

639
00:58:45,063 --> 00:58:46,565
They almost got you, huh?

640
00:58:47,357 --> 00:58:48,859
Climb in here.

641
00:58:51,778 --> 00:58:54,906
The question is totally without meaning.

642
00:58:56,199 --> 00:58:58,452
Pardon me, sir. Stuff.

643
00:58:59,995 --> 00:59:01,580
Thick and heavy.

644
00:59:01,830 --> 00:59:04,499
Would 60 gallons be sufficient?

645
00:59:05,125 --> 00:59:08,795
I rarely use it myself, sir.
It promotes rust.

646
00:59:19,306 --> 00:59:21,391
Don't worry, Giz, we'll find him.

647
01:01:39,321 --> 01:01:40,947
Gremlins, huh?

648
01:01:41,198 --> 01:01:43,158
- Little monsters.
- Right.

649
01:01:43,325 --> 01:01:47,579
- Hundreds of them?
- I'm not sure. Maybe thousands.

650
01:01:48,788 --> 01:01:51,791
Look, I know it sounds crazy.
I know it does.

651
01:01:52,000 --> 01:01:55,587
But in a matter of hours,
this town's gonna be a disaster area.

652
01:01:55,795 --> 01:01:57,255
You've got to warn people!

653
01:01:57,464 --> 01:02:00,508
- You think this kid is drunk?
- No, but you are.

654
01:02:00,967 --> 01:02:01,968
I am not drunk!

655
01:02:02,135 --> 01:02:06,348
Tell me something. Where do
these little gremlins come from?

656
01:02:06,723 --> 01:02:07,724
All right.

657
01:02:07,974 --> 01:02:11,353
My father gave me one as a present.

658
01:02:11,770 --> 01:02:15,106
Does your father always give
you vicious little monsters?

659
01:02:15,315 --> 01:02:18,109
No, they don't start out vicious at first!

660
01:02:18,318 --> 01:02:19,569
Of course not.

661
01:02:19,778 --> 01:02:23,031
They don't! They look like this.

662
01:02:24,282 --> 01:02:25,951
Could you dim the lights?

663
01:02:26,409 --> 01:02:27,661
Sure.

664
01:02:28,286 --> 01:02:30,497
Go ahead, Brent. Dim the lights.

665
01:02:40,507 --> 01:02:41,800
Gusto!

666
01:03:05,156 --> 01:03:06,825
Right, Murray?

667
01:03:16,167 --> 01:03:18,503
Sheila, will you quit
messing with the TV?

668
01:03:19,421 --> 01:03:21,423
You have the thingy.

669
01:03:25,844 --> 01:03:27,679
Goddamn foreign TV.

670
01:03:30,223 --> 01:03:32,017
We should've got a Zenith!

671
01:03:43,403 --> 01:03:44,654
Foreigners.

672
01:03:48,950 --> 01:03:51,036
I can't get a damn thing on this!

673
01:03:52,120 --> 01:03:53,121
Where are you going?

674
01:03:53,330 --> 01:03:56,541
I'm gonna check the antenna.
Maybe the damn thing blew down.

675
01:03:56,750 --> 01:03:58,460
Be careful, dear.

676
01:04:16,561 --> 01:04:18,355
What the hell is that?

677
01:05:04,776 --> 01:05:07,320
- It's them!
- You're crazy!

678
01:05:07,529 --> 01:05:10,281
There's a real gremlin in my cab!

679
01:05:42,147 --> 01:05:44,732
Hello, Anderson.
Wanna mail something, do you?

680
01:05:44,941 --> 01:05:46,943
Just a last-minute package, Father.

681
01:05:47,152 --> 01:05:48,486
Be my guest.

682
01:05:50,488 --> 01:05:51,990
That's strange.

683
01:06:21,394 --> 01:06:23,146
Patriotic little fellow, ain't he?

684
01:06:23,354 --> 01:06:25,356
Waving the flag and everything.

685
01:06:27,317 --> 01:06:30,111
Be careful, Frank!
He might tear your arm off.

686
01:06:30,320 --> 01:06:32,489
You want me to put the cuffs on him?

687
01:06:32,697 --> 01:06:35,241
Tell me. How come a cute guy like this...

688
01:06:35,450 --> 01:06:37,952
...can turn into a thousand ugly monsters?

689
01:06:38,161 --> 01:06:41,247
You see, this is before it
enters the pupal stage.

690
01:06:41,456 --> 01:06:42,707
It multiplies with water.

691
01:06:44,292 --> 01:06:47,003
- Get the kid some water.
- I wouldn't do that.

692
01:06:47,212 --> 01:06:48,713
Sheriff's office.

693
01:06:49,547 --> 01:06:50,798
Yeah, speaking.

694
01:06:53,051 --> 01:06:54,302
What?

695
01:06:56,679 --> 01:06:58,014
Oh, no.

696
01:06:58,723 --> 01:07:01,226
Yeah, sure, we'll be right over.

697
01:07:02,018 --> 01:07:03,311
What happened?

698
01:07:03,895 --> 01:07:05,146
The Futtermans.

699
01:07:05,688 --> 01:07:09,442
Something about a snowplow.
A freak accident.

700
01:07:09,651 --> 01:07:10,985
It's the creatures!

701
01:07:11,194 --> 01:07:14,572
The creatures are making it
look like an accident!

702
01:07:16,115 --> 01:07:17,408
Will you listen to me?

703
01:07:17,659 --> 01:07:19,369
You listen to me, kid!

704
01:07:19,744 --> 01:07:21,746
Go on home, take little Gizmo...

705
01:07:21,955 --> 01:07:25,250
...sit by the fireplace and open
your Christmas presents.

706
01:07:25,458 --> 01:07:26,876
Attaboy.

707
01:07:27,669 --> 01:07:29,546
- Let me drive.
- No, you're drunk.

708
01:07:29,754 --> 01:07:30,838
You always drive!

709
01:07:31,047 --> 01:07:33,258
Because I'm the sheriff, asshole.

710
01:07:49,190 --> 01:07:52,735
Kopeck, you stop that, you bad kitty!

711
01:07:53,319 --> 01:07:55,488
Kopeck's a bad kitty.

712
01:07:55,738 --> 01:07:57,949
Ruble's a good little kitty.

713
01:07:58,199 --> 01:08:03,329
We'll find you something to eat.
She's a good kitty.

714
01:08:06,040 --> 01:08:08,585
Here we go. Here we go. Come on.

715
01:08:08,793 --> 01:08:10,336
All right, you stop that!

716
01:08:10,545 --> 01:08:12,130
Stop it!

717
01:08:15,675 --> 01:08:19,053
Mean kitty, you start eating
before everybody gets here.

718
01:08:19,262 --> 01:08:20,930
Come on, Dollar Bill.

719
01:08:21,139 --> 01:08:23,850
Yes, here we go, Dollar Bill.

720
01:08:24,100 --> 01:08:27,312
Mommy'll fix you something good to eat.

721
01:08:27,520 --> 01:08:28,938
Everybody here?

722
01:08:29,188 --> 01:08:32,066
All right, let go of Mommy's coat.

723
01:08:32,275 --> 01:08:33,276
Here.

724
01:08:38,489 --> 01:08:40,491
Christmas carolers.

725
01:08:41,200 --> 01:08:43,870
I hate Christmas carolers.

726
01:08:44,120 --> 01:08:47,999
Screechy-voiced little glue-sniffers.

727
01:08:49,167 --> 01:08:51,753
I warned you brats!

728
01:08:52,879 --> 01:08:54,714
Ya-ya-ya! Ya-ya-ya!

729
01:09:06,893 --> 01:09:08,519
What are they?

730
01:09:08,728 --> 01:09:10,730
What are they?!

731
01:09:16,569 --> 01:09:17,987
They're here!

732
01:09:18,196 --> 01:09:21,366
They've come for me!
They've come!

733
01:09:24,243 --> 01:09:25,620
I'm not ready.

734
01:09:25,828 --> 01:09:28,831
I'm not ready yet.
I'm not ready!

735
01:09:54,399 --> 01:09:56,192
My God, Frye!

736
01:09:56,567 --> 01:09:57,985
That was Mrs. Deagle.

737
01:10:06,160 --> 01:10:08,871
Get them off! Get them off! Help me!

738
01:10:10,164 --> 01:10:13,000
That's Dave Myers.
He does Santa every year.

739
01:10:18,131 --> 01:10:20,174
What the hell is he doing now?

740
01:10:21,008 --> 01:10:23,094
What's that stuff
he's got all over him?

741
01:10:25,680 --> 01:10:27,890
Frank, I really think we should go now.

742
01:10:28,099 --> 01:10:31,269
Start the car. I'd really like
to go back to the station.

743
01:10:32,854 --> 01:10:34,105
Please!

744
01:10:37,650 --> 01:10:38,735
Frank!

745
01:11:02,592 --> 01:11:04,135
Jesus, Frank!

746
01:11:04,343 --> 01:11:05,970
What the hell are those things?

747
01:11:08,014 --> 01:11:10,600
It's Christmas.
What the hell's going on?

748
01:11:10,808 --> 01:11:11,934
Shut up, will you?!

749
01:11:40,254 --> 01:11:41,923
I don't believe it.

750
01:11:46,427 --> 01:11:48,262
<i>You're on with Rockin' Ricky! Go!</i>

751
01:11:48,471 --> 01:11:50,223
<i>Hi, my name's Pete.</i>

752
01:11:50,431 --> 01:11:53,476
<i>These green guys are running
around wrecking things.</i>

753
01:11:53,684 --> 01:11:56,103
<i>This is Christmas, not Halloween!</i>

754
01:11:56,354 --> 01:11:57,396
<i>Listen, gang.</i>

755
01:11:57,688 --> 01:12:00,900
<i>Rockin' Ricky's getting fed up
with this Orson Welles crap!</i>

756
01:12:01,108 --> 01:12:04,821
<i>What's that? Kitty, what's that?
Some of Rockin' Ricky fans?</i>

757
01:12:05,196 --> 01:12:07,615
<i>You're not a Rockin' Ricky fan!</i>

758
01:12:31,889 --> 01:12:35,393
Sir, I notice that you're a smoker.

759
01:12:36,143 --> 01:12:39,939
I notice that you're a smoker.
I see the cigarettes.

760
01:12:40,898 --> 01:12:43,484
I noticed, here, this broken ashtray.

761
01:12:44,485 --> 01:12:47,113
It's very fortunate
that I happened to come by.

762
01:12:47,280 --> 01:12:51,075
Let me introduce myself.
My name's Randall Peltzer. I'm an inventor.

763
01:12:51,284 --> 01:12:54,620
"Fantastic Ideas for a Fantastic World."
I make the illogical logical.

764
01:12:54,787 --> 01:12:58,416
I have something here that I think
you might be interested in.

765
01:12:59,000 --> 01:13:00,626
Yes, sir, I do.

766
01:13:00,960 --> 01:13:02,461
This is...

767
01:13:02,920 --> 01:13:05,298
...the Peltzer Smokeless Ashtray.

768
01:13:05,464 --> 01:13:08,467
I think this can solve
your problem here, sir.

769
01:14:01,020 --> 01:14:03,189
Please don't bite me!

770
01:14:04,357 --> 01:14:05,691
Wait a minute.

771
01:17:31,730 --> 01:17:32,731
You all right?

772
01:17:32,898 --> 01:17:34,400
Let's get out of here!

773
01:17:37,862 --> 01:17:39,071
What's that?

774
01:17:39,238 --> 01:17:42,158
Don't worry. He's with me.
He's not one of them.

775
01:17:48,164 --> 01:17:50,708
What's wrong?
Why isn't the car starting?

776
01:17:51,542 --> 01:17:54,044
We're gonna have to make
a run for it, okay?

777
01:17:54,253 --> 01:17:56,589
One, two, three!

778
01:18:30,956 --> 01:18:32,625
They've been here too.

779
01:18:33,459 --> 01:18:36,337
What are these things?
Where do they come from?

780
01:18:37,796 --> 01:18:39,715
They're gremlins, Kate.

781
01:18:40,966 --> 01:18:43,260
Just like Mr. Futterman said.

782
01:18:49,850 --> 01:18:52,436
Now I have another reason
to hate Christmas.

783
01:18:53,312 --> 01:18:54,813
What are you talking about?

784
01:18:55,773 --> 01:19:00,319
The worst thing that ever happened
to me was on Christmas.

785
01:19:00,986 --> 01:19:03,322
Oh, God. It was so horrible.

786
01:19:06,825 --> 01:19:08,661
It was Christmas Eve.

787
01:19:09,328 --> 01:19:10,996
I was 9 years old.

788
01:19:12,498 --> 01:19:15,292
Me and Mom were decorating the tree...

789
01:19:16,001 --> 01:19:18,045
...waiting for Dad
to come home from work.

790
01:19:19,838 --> 01:19:21,632
A couple hours went by.

791
01:19:21,840 --> 01:19:23,509
Dad wasn't home.

792
01:19:23,884 --> 01:19:26,512
So Mom called the office.
No answer.

793
01:19:27,972 --> 01:19:32,685
Christmas Day came and went,
and still nothing.

794
01:19:34,395 --> 01:19:36,647
So the police began a search.

795
01:19:37,189 --> 01:19:39,400
Four or five days went by.

796
01:19:39,692 --> 01:19:42,486
Neither one of us could eat or sleep.

797
01:19:43,362 --> 01:19:45,322
Everything was falling apart.

798
01:19:47,032 --> 01:19:48,701
It was snowing outside.

799
01:19:49,660 --> 01:19:54,039
The house was freezing, so I went
to try to light up the fire.

800
01:19:54,206 --> 01:19:56,417
That's when I noticed the smell.

801
01:20:00,838 --> 01:20:03,716
The firemen came and broke
through the chimney top.

802
01:20:03,882 --> 01:20:08,053
And me and Mom were expecting
them to pull out a dead cat or a bird.

803
01:20:08,304 --> 01:20:11,056
And instead they pulled out my father.

804
01:20:15,394 --> 01:20:18,731
He was dressed in a Santa Claus suit.

805
01:20:19,606 --> 01:20:22,109
He'd been climbing down the chimney...

806
01:20:22,359 --> 01:20:24,611
...his arms loaded with presents.

807
01:20:25,237 --> 01:20:27,072
He was gonna surprise us.

808
01:20:29,825 --> 01:20:33,370
He slipped and broke his neck.
He died instantly.

809
01:20:37,583 --> 01:20:40,419
And that's how I found out
there was no Santa Claus.

810
01:20:44,214 --> 01:20:47,760
Don't worry about that smoke.
It'll stop. It's guaranteed.

811
01:20:58,228 --> 01:20:59,730
Barney, shut up!

812
01:20:59,938 --> 01:21:02,358
Don't start with me.
I got a long way to go.

813
01:21:03,067 --> 01:21:04,151
Shut up!

814
01:21:59,998 --> 01:22:01,333
Where did they all go?

815
01:22:01,542 --> 01:22:03,335
It'll be light soon.

816
01:22:03,502 --> 01:22:05,712
I bet they're all together someplace dark.

817
01:22:14,304 --> 01:22:15,722
<i>Mogwai</i>!

818
01:22:25,941 --> 01:22:28,193
Shh, Gizmo.

819
01:22:45,878 --> 01:22:47,337
They're inside.

820
01:22:47,546 --> 01:22:48,964
All of them?

821
01:22:55,220 --> 01:22:56,680
Milk Duds.

822
01:24:18,262 --> 01:24:19,680
What are they doing?

823
01:24:21,139 --> 01:24:23,141
They're watching <i>Snow White</i>.

824
01:24:24,101 --> 01:24:25,769
And they love it.

825
01:24:33,610 --> 01:24:35,070
Where's the boiler room?

826
01:24:35,279 --> 01:24:36,989
It's in the back of the theater.

827
01:24:50,794 --> 01:24:52,170
Down there.

828
01:25:02,180 --> 01:25:03,181
Milk Duds.

829
01:25:26,747 --> 01:25:29,166
Yum, yum.

830
01:25:39,885 --> 01:25:42,387
Cover your mouth.
Don't breathe any gas.

831
01:25:57,402 --> 01:25:58,487
Billy!

832
01:25:58,654 --> 01:25:59,905
Go.

833
01:26:23,261 --> 01:26:24,429
Billy!

834
01:26:42,406 --> 01:26:43,573
Billy!

835
01:26:45,117 --> 01:26:48,954
- Hurry up!
- Move, Katie! Watch out!

836
01:26:51,456 --> 01:26:52,916
Come on!

837
01:27:31,997 --> 01:27:32,998
Billy...

838
01:27:33,373 --> 01:27:35,459
In the department store.

839
01:27:36,460 --> 01:27:37,794
Stripe!

840
01:28:06,823 --> 01:28:09,493
That's Stripe. He's the leader.

841
01:28:12,037 --> 01:28:14,873
If he gets to water,
it'll start all over again.

842
01:28:31,807 --> 01:28:36,561
Take Giz, go back and try and
find some kind of light switch.

843
01:28:48,240 --> 01:28:50,075
Careful, Billy.

844
01:30:00,937 --> 01:30:03,189
<i>Ward is your snowplow headquarters.</i>

845
01:30:27,672 --> 01:30:29,424
<i>Attention, Christmas shoppers.</i>

846
01:30:29,633 --> 01:30:34,471
<i>Saturday morning at 8:30, we'll have
Santa Claus for all the kiddies.</i>

847
01:30:49,319 --> 01:30:51,655
<i>We have the Kingston Falls...</i>

848
01:30:53,073 --> 01:30:54,699
<i>Attention, shoppers.</i>

849
01:32:17,574 --> 01:32:19,242
Light bright!

850
01:32:26,666 --> 01:32:28,835
Bye-bye.

851
01:33:26,976 --> 01:33:28,895
<i>It takes a certain kind of guy.</i>

852
01:33:29,104 --> 01:33:31,940
<i>And that guy needs
a certain kind of dame.</i>

853
01:34:26,661 --> 01:34:29,581
Water!

854
01:34:32,500 --> 01:34:33,585
Gun!

855
01:34:34,169 --> 01:34:36,963
<i>It's been a rough night
for Rockin' Ricky...</i>

856
01:34:37,672 --> 01:34:40,550
<i>...but he's still on the air!</i>

857
01:34:40,925 --> 01:34:43,887
<i>The Marines are standing by
with fire hoses.</i>

858
01:35:30,600 --> 01:35:32,393
Billy.

859
01:36:26,948 --> 01:36:29,450
Gizmo ca-ca!

860
01:36:29,659 --> 01:36:31,703
Light bright! Light bright!

861
01:37:10,700 --> 01:37:13,036
What the hell is that?

862
01:37:25,089 --> 01:37:26,090
Your scarf.

863
01:38:29,362 --> 01:38:30,822
<i>We switch to a report...</i>

864
01:38:31,030 --> 01:38:34,075
<i>...from the scene
of the Christmas Eve riots.</i>

865
01:38:35,618 --> 01:38:39,580
<i>This is Lew Landers,
WDHB's Action Central News...</i>

866
01:38:39,789 --> 01:38:41,833
<i>...at the site of Dorry's Tavern...</i>

867
01:38:42,208 --> 01:38:45,628
<i>...or what used to be Dorry's Tavern,
in Kingston Falls...</i>

868
01:38:45,837 --> 01:38:47,255
<i>...where officials blame...</i>

869
01:38:47,463 --> 01:38:51,342
<i>...mass hysteria for the escalating
series of unexplained...</i>

870
01:38:51,551 --> 01:38:55,930
<i>...accidents, fires and explosions
that rocked this once-peaceful town...</i>

871
01:38:56,472 --> 01:38:57,932
<i>...on Christmas Eve.</i>

872
01:38:58,141 --> 01:39:01,227
<i>The bizarre demise
of Mrs. Ruby Deagle, widow...</i>

873
01:39:01,436 --> 01:39:04,772
...of convicted stock-swindler
Donald Deagle...

874
01:39:05,231 --> 01:39:07,150
Don't chew that.

875
01:39:07,400 --> 01:39:08,693
Don't chew.

876
01:39:11,279 --> 01:39:13,573
I bet he'd like some chicken soup.

877
01:39:19,203 --> 01:39:23,499
Honey, this is the gentleman
who sold me the <i>mogwai</i>.

878
01:39:24,000 --> 01:39:27,879
"Sold." An interesting choice of words.

879
01:39:32,258 --> 01:39:35,678
<i>Conflicting eyewitness reports
concerning "little green men"...</i>

880
01:39:38,181 --> 01:39:42,268
You teach him to watch television?

881
01:39:48,191 --> 01:39:50,818
There was, I believe, a box.

882
01:40:00,411 --> 01:40:01,579
Dad...

883
01:40:12,048 --> 01:40:13,758
Rand, your scarf.

884
01:40:15,801 --> 01:40:16,969
I warned you.

885
01:40:17,595 --> 01:40:20,890
With <i>mogwai</i> comes much responsibility.

886
01:40:21,140 --> 01:40:22,558
But you didn't listen.

887
01:40:22,808 --> 01:40:25,144
And you see what happens.

888
01:40:25,353 --> 01:40:27,188
I didn't mean it.

889
01:40:27,396 --> 01:40:30,816
You do with <i>mogwai</i> what your society...

890
01:40:31,067 --> 01:40:35,196
...has done with all of nature's gifts.

891
01:40:35,404 --> 01:40:37,532
You do not understand.

892
01:40:39,992 --> 01:40:41,369
You are not ready.

893
01:40:52,171 --> 01:40:53,714
- Papa?
- Yes?

894
01:40:57,301 --> 01:40:59,512
He has something to say to you.

895
01:41:06,060 --> 01:41:08,854
You understand what he says
when he speaks to you?

896
01:41:09,063 --> 01:41:12,358
To hear, one has only to listen.

897
01:41:16,195 --> 01:41:17,780
Bye, Billy.

898
01:41:23,786 --> 01:41:26,831
Perhaps someday you may be ready.

899
01:41:27,039 --> 01:41:28,958
Until then, <i>mogwai</i>...

900
01:41:29,375 --> 01:41:30,918
...will be waiting.

901
01:41:34,130 --> 01:41:35,506
Excuse me, sir.

902
01:41:36,382 --> 01:41:38,467
Before you go, I wanted to tell you...

903
01:41:38,718 --> 01:41:41,512
...that I am truly sorry
for what's happened.

904
01:41:42,013 --> 01:41:44,932
And if you would accept it,
I'd like to...

905
01:41:45,141 --> 01:41:47,143
...give you this small token.

906
01:41:47,435 --> 01:41:50,730
There's one other one.
This is an invention of mine.

907
01:41:50,938 --> 01:41:52,982
Smokeless Ashtray.

908
01:41:53,190 --> 01:41:54,233
How did you know?

909
01:41:54,442 --> 01:41:57,361
Man at gas station tried to sell me.

910
01:41:57,612 --> 01:42:00,323
Latest word in technology.

911
01:42:00,906 --> 01:42:03,075
Very generous of you.

912
01:42:03,284 --> 01:42:06,162
I'm sure it will come in handy.

913
01:42:12,918 --> 01:42:14,712
Bye-bye, woof-woof.

914
01:42:32,313 --> 01:42:34,607
<i>Well, that's the story.</i>

915
01:42:35,191 --> 01:42:39,737
<i>So if your air conditioner goes on the fritz,
your washing machine blows up...</i>

916
01:42:39,945 --> 01:42:42,406
<i>...or your video recorder conks out...</i>

917
01:42:42,615 --> 01:42:44,659
<i>...before you call the repairman...</i>

918
01:42:44,992 --> 01:42:48,287
<i>...turn on the lights,
check the closets and cupboards...</i>

919
01:42:48,788 --> 01:42:50,873
<i>...look under all the beds.</i>

920
01:42:51,082 --> 01:42:53,125
<i>Because you never can tell.</i>

921
01:42:53,959 --> 01:42:57,672
<i>There just might be
a gremlin in your house.</i>

